   "body" : "I opened this in WIP stage in order to get feedback and sort out the conceptual problems.\r\n\r\nWhat this PR does:\r\n* Topup the keypool during wallet init\r\n* Warn if the key pool size is smaller then the recommended size to not miss funds in a restore\r\n* Warns if the wallet is locked\r\n* Detectes if the keypool keys where used in a `IsMine` or `IsFromMe` tx during `SyncTransaction`\r\n** Marks all keys in the key pool on the corresponding chain (internal/external) as used\r\n** Topsup the keypool\r\n\r\nWhat is missing:\r\n* Better handling of locked wallets\r\n* Not sure what how to react in the following use case:\r\n** SyncTransactions finds an output that matched keypool index 10\r\n** Wallet markes keypool 0-10 as used\r\n** SyncTransactions finds an output that matched keypool index 1 (already marked as used)\r\n** Funds getting detected, but wallet missed to set the \"receive\" category\r\n\r\nAlso, I'm not sure if we should explicit detect if a wallet is in \"restore-state\" (would be possible by comparing the wallet best block against the chain tip). In that case, we could warn better, use a larger keypool size, etc.\r\n\r\nThanks for feedback!",
